<item>
            <title>[LU-9153] improve FID/config name specification for lctl llog_print and llog_info</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9153</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Current llog name specification is totally non-standard for &lt;tt&gt;lctl llog_print&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;llog_info&lt;/tt&gt;, and related commands.  Change this to optionally accept config llog names without the leading &apos;$&apos;, since adding &apos;$&apos; is non-intuitive and the shell will think this is a variable and &quot;&lt;tt&gt;$fsname-client&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; becomes &quot;&lt;tt&gt;-client&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Similarly, llog identifiers are formatted like &quot;&lt;tt&gt;#0x4:10#0000000&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; instead of the standard FID format &lt;tt&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0x4:0x10:0x0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;.  Update the code to print FIDs in standard format.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
